values:
Really?



this better be good, and I have subjective hankering that it will be

p.s. hey guess what? 2008. Exciiitement-&nbsp;

We'll talk.&nbsp;

&lt;3 peace, my loves
and a very Happy New Year! bombastically heartfelt rather than casual greeting, tingles. Egad!

Arttttttttttttttttty art art&nbsp;

superflooding relief and concentration effort ease familiarity difficulty new laughing&nbsp;smiling happy messy goopy delight
finally.

My oils class started, at last. We painted done at Rock today. It shall be once a week until the first week in August, annnd (this is bizarre) I can't wait for the next monday. Ish. I want to get some stuff accomplished before then. ..but more paint wonderfulness.....yesss.

Sorry. I do in fact realize that I am being completely nonsensical right now -however. This was so much what I needed right now, I can barely describe it.&nbsp;
Being plunged back into something that I love, that's challenging and new but in a familiar way, where everyone is crazy, liberal, and NICE and no one tells you to work out and there's no seniority issues, only admiration for people who know what they're doing -- ahhhhhh


The class itself is going to be in a different location outside each week, with the beautiful late afternoon sun (or haze, as the case was this week. Equally lovely, actually). It's about 2ish hours long, so you have to work pretty quickly and brutally, and think on your feet. as it were. It's really different from school art, where you're doused in 30 minute segments of work time a couple times a week while thinking about trig homework and bomb threats. There are 8 of us in the class, plus my crazy (ain't they all?) teacher, Trish. The catch is that 6 are at least 50 years old, and some older. One other girl is about 20ish. And then there's me. No problem, though. It's so cool in and of itself that a) this doesn't bother them or me b) we're all there to learn and paint ...and. and. Ladies and Gents, I am thrilled, euphorically content and SOUPED for next week (norman bird).&nbsp;

[oh and did I mention she liked what I did giggle tehee? Positive reinforcement, delish! I am not entirely a waste of human, hooraaay! tehee again.]


On other notes:
Happy belated 4th, y'all. We celebrate our toddler country (think terrible twos, going around with new skills, and smashing things) with explosions, and that suits me fine. I may get some of my fav pics up that I've taken recently, fireworks and otherwise. I may not.&nbsp;

Camping trips, plural -- should happen this summer, no? Name dates you know for sure you will be gone, please. The sooner the better, we don't actually have that much time, which is startling.

this time last year, I was getting ready to pack it all in and head overseas. Last year?

Next dance in the works, ish. Aquidneck school, methinks. Please and thankyou for the repeated coming and supporting :)

If you have siblings, friends of any age, yourself, whatever - I want to start giving more fiddle lessons. For one, it'll make sure I don't slack off. Two, it's another thing I like and that seems worthwhile. Vs, you know. That whole lifeguarding crap.&nbsp;

Lifeguarding. Frustrating? beautiful setting, easy enough job, and plenty of good people, and good enough pay. Need to work my head around the couple of things rubbing raw. Or find a fairy dust mine. Preferred.

Craft booth for the fall shows - we should plan this further, as we all have spare time now, sort of.&nbsp;

Sewing! Yaaaay! Good nights, bad nights? Also needs to swing into action.

I've decided that I'm turning my brain back on, ish. It sort of died there for a little while. Screw buoy swims, life is grand.&nbsp;

love y'all
